parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift gears
the transmission may fail without warning
causing the vehicle to slow down or come to a sudden stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch master cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Instrument panel gauge failure can cause the driver to lose visibility of important vehicle information, such as speed, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The instrument panel gauges fail to function
making it difficult or impossible for the driver to see important vehicle information.
